{
  "stem": "9590.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] My father was a wonderful person.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I suppose every child will say it about her father.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But when I look back, I see that he had a lot of foresight and a lot of enterprise in him to do things that not the ordinary people would do.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] In the early 30s, my father bought a piece of land.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "It was a very beautiful, choice piece of land.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And he remarked that if he would invest in money, in a bank, the money can devalue it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Or, if he would buy real estate, when there is a war, it can be destroyed, but land will always have its value.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "As long as the world will exist, the land will be land.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And then he remarked to my mother, we are sure we'll have dowry for our [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I was very young then, but he was thinking in terms of the future.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Now, when the Soviet Union occupied our territory, [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] we were considered also farmers because we owned land.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] So the Soviet regime took-- took from the private hands.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "They took the land and made kolkhoz, it's collective farming.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And somehow they trusted my father, and my father became the president of the kolkhoz.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] It was an unheard of situation, because he was a businessman, a well-to-do.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "According to the Soviet laws, he wasn't even supposed to be trusted.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "But the people in the-- in our vicinity that dealt with my father and the business felt that he was a very honorable man, and he is fit for that position.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
